hooting of ''[[The Bridge on the River Kwai]]''\nFile:George Lucas and Chandran Rutnam.jpeg|[[George Lucas]] and Chandran Rutnam\nFile:Chandran Rutnam with John and Bo Derek.jpeg|Chandran Rutnam with [[John Derek]] and [[Bo Derek]]\nFile:Harrison Ford and Chandran Rutnam in Sri Lanka.jpg|[[Harrison Ford]] and Chandran Rutnam on the set of ''[[Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom]]'' which was shot in Hantana, Sri Lanka in 1983\nFile:Steven Spielberg with Chandran Rutnam in Sri Lanka.jpg|[[Steven Spielberg]] and Chandran Rutnam on location in Sri Lanka during the filming of ''[[Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom]]''\nFile:Chandranratnum2.JPG|Rutnam with [[Steven Spielberg]] at a benefit honoring Spielberg (December 9, 2009)\nFile:Anton Wickremasinghe, Chandran Rutnam and Alfred Hitchcock at the Academy Awards in Los Angeles.jpeg|Anton Wickremasinghe, Chandran Rutnam (center) and [[Alfred Hitchcock]] at the [[Academy Awards]] in Los Angeles.\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Evelyn Rutnam Institute for Inter-Cultural Studies]]\n* [[Cinema of Sri Lanka]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Chandran Rutnam}}\n* {{IMDb name|0752110}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gs99BJEs6Kc ''Uththareethara: Chandran Rutnam'' (documentary video)]\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{Sinhala Cinema|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rutnam, Chandran}}\n[[Category:Sri Lankan Tamil film directors]]\n[[Category:Sinhalese people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English-language film directors]]\n[[Category:Film producers from California]]\n[[Category:American film directors of Sri Lankan descent]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan Tamil film producers]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n[[Category:American film editors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Chandran Rutnam\n| image       = File:Chandran Rutnam - The Road from Elephant Pass crop.JPG\n| image_size  = \n| caption     = Rutnam in 2006\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = \n| birth_place = [[Ceylon]]\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| death_cause =\n| resting_place =\n| resting_place_coordinates =\n| residence   =\n| nationality = [[Sri Lankan people|Sri Lankan]]\n| other_names =\n| known_for   = [[Film-making]]\n| education   =\n| occupation  = [[Film director]], [[Film producer|producer]], [[screenwriter]], [[entrepreneur]]\n| title       = President and CEO of Asian Film Locations Services<br>Ex-Chairman of [[Lionair]]<br>Chairman of [[Asian Aviation Centre (Sri Lanka)|Asian Aviation Centre]] \n| height      =\n| weight      =\n| spouse      =\n| children    = James, Daniel, Evelyn, Chanel, Danara\n| website     = [http://www.filmlocationservices.lk Asian Film Locations Services]<br>[http://www.aac.lk Asian Aviation Centre]\n}}\n\n'''Chandran Rutnam''' is a  [[Sri Lanka|Sri Lankan Film maker]]  and entrepreneur.<ref name=\"dnr\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.dailynews.lk/?q=features/rutnam-movies|title= RUTNAM: like in the movies|accessdate= April 2, 2015|work= Daily News|date= September 25, 2013|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141203180304/http://www.dailynews.lk/?q=features%2Frutnam-movies|archivedate= December 3, 2014|df= mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"SOBRB\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2007/02/11/imp07.asp |title= Breaking the artificial barriers |accessdate= April 2, 2015 |work= Sunday Observer |date= February 11, 2007 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110722150107/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2007/02/11/imp07.asp |archivedate= July 22, 2011 |df= mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nRutnam has hosted numerous [[Hollywood]] films for their location shoots in Sri Lanka and [[Malaysia]].<ref name=\"dnr\"/><ref name=\"SOBRB\"/> He was the Line Producer/Production Supervisor on several international productions including the Sri Lankan location shoot of [[Paramount Pictures]]' ''[[Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom]]'' (1984) and ''[[Indochine (film)|Indochine]]'' (1992).<ref name=\"dnr\"/><ref name=\"SOBRB\"/> He is the President and Chief Executive Officer of the Asian Film Location Services which mostly hosts foreign films to be shot in South and South East Asia.\n\n[[Steven Spielberg]] once referred to Rutnam as \"Our most valued friend in the Far East\".<ref name=\"SOBRB\"/><ref name=NS/><ref name=BJ/><ref name=\"Hollywood gets Tsunami plea\">{{Cite web|url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4186727.stm |title= Hollywood gets Tsunami plea|accessdate=February 5, 2008 |work= BBC | date=January 19, 2005}}</ref> Rutnam has also worked with [[Sir David Lean]], [[Sir Carol Reed]], [[John Boorman]], [[George Lucas]] and [[Regis Wargnier]].<ref name=\"dnr\"/>\n\nRutnam wrote the screenplay, produced, directed and edited the film ''[[The Road from Elephant Pass (film)|The Road from Elephant Pass]]'', which was a Finalist Award Winner at the New York International Television and Film Awards in 2011.<ref name=NS/><ref name=BJ/> He also wrote the adapted screenplay and produced and directed, ''[[A Common Man (film)|A Common Man]]'' which starred [[Sir Ben Kingsley]] and [[Ben Cross]]. The film was nominated for the four main awards at the Madrid International Film Festival in 2013, winning the Best Picture, Best Director and the Best Actor awards.<ref name=\"dnr\"/><ref name=\"MFF\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=83141|title= Lankans' film wins three awards|accessdate=July 9, 2013 |work= The Island | date=July 8, 2013}}</ref>\n\nRutnam was the founder of [[Lionair]], a deceased Sri Lankan airline, and owns the [[Asian Aviation Centre (Sri Lanka)|Asian Aviation Centre]], an aeronautical engineering and flying academy. {{Citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n==Family==\nRutnam was born to a [[Sri Lankan Tamil|Tamil]] father Dr. [[James T. Rutnam]] and a [[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]] mother Evelyn Wijeyaratne. He lived in [[Los Angeles, California]] for 38 years and now resides in [[Colombo, Sri Lanka]]. He is a brother of [[Jayam Rutnam]], the founder of the Sri Lanka America Association of Southern California (SLAASC).<ref name=\"dnr\"/>\n\n[[File:Asian Aviation Hangar.JPG|right|250px|thumb|Rutnam at the [[hangar]] of [[Asian Aviation Centre (Sri Lanka)|Asian Aviation Centre]] and [[Lionair]]]]\n\n==Life and career==\nRutnam was a school boy when David Lean arrived in Sri Lanka to shoot his [[Second World War]] epic, ''[[The Bridge on the River Kwai]]''. The film crew hired a house that belonged to his parents for the shooting.<ref name=NS>{{Cite web|url= http://www.hinduonnet.com/mag/2005/04/17/stories/2005041700600800.htm |title= Dream locales in Lanka|accessdate=February 4, 2008 |work= Nirupama Subramaniam}}</ref><ref name=BJ>{{Cite web|url= http://www.sundaytimes.lk/980524/plus6.html|title= Moving movie man dreams on|accessdate=February 4, 2008 |work= Bandula Jayasekara}}</ref> Due to this exposure, to the consternation of his parents, he dropped out of school and went to London to pursue his dream of a career in films. He later moved to the [[United States]] and attended the film school at the [[University of Southern California]] and the San Fernando Valley College of Law. While working in Hollywood studios, Rutnam's break in selling Sri Lankan locations to international filmmakers came when he managed to convince [[John Derek]], director of ''[[Tarzan, the Ape Man (1981 film)|Tarzan the Apeman]]'', to shoot the film in Sri Lanka rather than in Africa.<ref name=NS/><ref name=BJ/><ref name=\"Hollywood gets Tsunami plea\"/>\n\nRutnam also dreamt of making a mark in the [[aviation]] field. He said \"I was the sort of guy who would go to an [[airport]] and watch the planes taking off. I remember as a kid, I went to the [[Colombo]] port and watched the ships coming and going out. I do not know whether it was wanderlust or freedom of movement. I do not know which one it was. Some years ago a friend of mine and I decided that we should have an [[airline]].\" <ref name=DN1>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2009/08/31/bus34.asp \n |title=Demand for local pilots increasing \n |accessdate=2011-04-29 \n |work=The Associated Newspapers of Ceylon Ltd. \n |date=2009-08-31 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019104733/http://www.dailynews.lk/2009/08/31/bus34.asp \n |archivedate=October 19, 2012 \n |df=mdy \n}}</ref> He founded [[Asian Aviation Centre (Sri Lanka)|Asian Aviation Centre]] and [[Lionair]]. Lionair was established in October 1993 and started its operations on 24 October 1994. Lionair suspended its domestic services when an [[Antonov An-24]] aircraft went missing shortly after it took off from [[Jaffna]] in 1998, but resumed services in October 2002.<ref name=\"FI\">[[Flight International]] 5\u201311 April 2005</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Theatrical releases===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:33px;\"| Year !! Film !! style=\"width:65px;\"| [[Film director|Director]] !! width=65 | [[Film producer|Producer]] !! width=65 | [[Screenwriter|Writer]] !! width=65 |[[Film editing|Editor]] !! width=65 |Other !! Notes\n|-\n|| 1981\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Tarzan, the Ape Man (1981 film)|Tarzan, the Ape Man]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1984\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]] \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Adara Kathawa''\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1986\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Lord Mountbatten: The Last Viceroy]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''The Kiss of the Cobra''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|| 1987\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Der Stein des Todes]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1988\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Farewell to the King]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''The Further Adventures of Tennessee Buck''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[A Dangerous Life]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1989\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[The Iron Triangle (film)|The Iron Triangle]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Shadow of the Cobra]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1990\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Witness to a Killing - Janelaya''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Ghosts Can't Do It]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Associate Producer]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1992\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Spooks''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Indochine (film)|Indochine]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n| [[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Fifty/Fifty (1992 film)|Fifty/Fifty]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]] \n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1993\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''La porte du ciel''<br>''(fran\u00e7ais)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n| [[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Le prix d'une femme''<br>''(fran\u00e7ais)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n| [[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Poronduwa]] - The Promise''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|-\n||1994\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Le Livre De Cristal''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" |1995\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Madara Parasathu''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Beyond Rangoon]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''L'enfant des Rues''<br>''(fran\u00e7ais)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|1996\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Robo Warriors''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Bloodsport 2]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Victory (1996 film)|Victory]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Caught (1996 film)|Caught]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|1997\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Les myst\u00e8res de Sadjurah''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Paradise Road (1997 film)|Paradise Road]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Bloodsport III]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[The Second Jungle Book: Mowgli & Baloo]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Associate Producer]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Mother Teresa: In the Name of God's Poor]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1998\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''D'or et de Safran''<br>''(fran\u00e7ais)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''The Son of Sandokan''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[:it:Iqbal|Iqbal]]<br>(Italino)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n|| 1999\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Pilgrimage - Theertha Yathra''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2000\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Stra\u00dfe ins Paradies''<br>''(Deutsch)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Der Kaptan''<br>''(Deutsch)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n||2001\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Un dono Semplice''<br>''(Italino)''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2002\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Mansion by the Lake - Wekanda Walauwa''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Love 2002''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''The Hostages''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n| [[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2003\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Mother Teresa of Calcutta (film)|Mother Teresa of Calcutta]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[The Sleeping Dictionary]]''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2006\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Spie Lies & Alibis''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Water (2005 film)|Water]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Production manager (theatre)|Production Manager]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''Fisherman's Daughter \u2013 Dheewari''\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2009\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Victory (2009 film)|Victory]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{yes}}\n|[[Film crew#Production Management|Production Supervisor]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[The Road from